{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Approved Luca as Step 9 driver, a11y preview",
    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED on Luca continuing as Driver for Step 9.\n\nStep 9 (Clarify as Waiting For) adds a new clarify path from inbox items to the Waiting For list. From an accessibility perspective, I'll be watching for:\n\n1. The clarify form needs a new radio button option for \"Waiting For\" alongside existing options (Next Action, Project, Trash). The radio group must remain properly labelled.\n2. When \"Waiting For\" is selected, the revealed fields (\"What are you waiting for?\" title and \"Who or what?\" waiting_on) need visible labels — same pattern as the add form we just reviewed.\n3. Progressive disclosure: fields revealed by radio selection must be accessible to screen readers (not just visually hidden/shown — use appropriate technique so AT picks up the change).\n4. After clarifying as Waiting For, the inbox count badge should update and focus should be managed correctly.\n\nLuca built the Waiting For feature so continuing as Driver makes sense. Ready to review when code is ready."
  }
}
